CHOLERA, DIARRHEA AND DYSENTERY UPDATE 2012 (23): CUBA (GRANMA) REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
***************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Fri 29 Jun 2012
Source: UPI (United Press International) [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
http://espanol.upi.com/Noticias-destacadas/2012/06/29/Periodistas-independientes-reportan-brote-de-c%C3%B3lera-en-oriente-de-Cuba/UPI-85681341022753/


Independent journalists reported on the deaths of 2 people and the hospitalization of about 50 as a result of an outbreak of cholera in the Cuban municipality of Manzanillo. The health emergency started in midweek. Cuban government officials have made no mention of the crisis but it has been learned that the municipality of Manzanillo, in the eastern province of Granma, has been declared in "quarantine".

The Provincial Clinical and Surgical Hospital "Celia Sanchez Manduley", where the patients with reported cholera were admitted, is guarded by state security agents and police officers, according to a report by journalist Calixto R Martinez. The report was published on the website of the "Hablemos Press" [Let's Talk Press] news agency, based in Havana.

According to the daily El Nuevo Herald [Miami], local residents interviewed by Martinez agreed that the situation has exceeded the capacity of the hospital, and commented that health authorities are seeking help from other municipalities.

--
